node.title: Live: Officials to release latest COVID case numbers
node.content: ["New Zealand reported just 29 new cases of COVID-19 on Saturday, leaving the seven-day tally at 25.\n", "No deaths were reported, with the country's fatality toll from coronavirus remaining at 52.", "It comes as New Zealand officials prepare for the highly-infectious Omicron variant to leak into the community. Since December 1, there have been nearly 300 Omicron infections detected in managed isolation.", "The Ministry of Health will provide Sunday's case numbers at 1pm. Follow Newshub's live updates below.", "12:55pm - Kia ora, good afternoon and welcome to Newshub's live COVID-19 updates for Sunday. Stand by as we bring you the latest COVID-19 case data, expected at 1pm."]
